purpose:
(Clinical Focus: Food Allergen),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify food allergen substances.),(Inclusion Criteria: We considered all color additives to be food additives, even though there could be other types of exposures from these substances.),(Exclusion Criteria: We exclude the "Generic" Food Allergen Group due to ambiguity. We exclude all qualifier value terms (e.g., sprinkle, gum) as these are not ideal for coding food allergen substances. We exclude inactive concepts. We did not consider vitamins,
herbals, enteral nutrition, or  parenteral nutrition as part of the food allergy list, because these substances are typically entered as drug allergies. We recognize that insects (eg, grasshoppers and bees) are a food substance in some parts of the world; however, in our analysis we considered these to be environmental allergens rather than food allergens, because environmental exposure was the more common type of exposure for our patient population.)
